ine-maillet-dead.html</link><description>她向加拿大一个被忽视的法语人口发出了声音，适应了通过口头传统幸存的古语言。</description><pubDate>Fri, 28 Feb 2025 22:10:52 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2025/02/28/books/antonine-maillet-dead.html</guid></item><item><title>读书俱乐部播客：萨曼莎·哈维（Samantha Harvey）的“轨道”</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2025/02/28/books/review/podcast-orbital-samantha-harvey-book-club.html</link><description>哈维（Harvey）的小说大约六名宇航员在国际空间站生活和工作，获得了2024年布克奖。</description><pubDate>Fri, 28 Feb 2025 23:10:48 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2025/02/28/books/review/podcast-orbital-samantha-harvey-book-club.html</guid></item><item><title>玛丽说了她说的“评论：催眠的huppert</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2025/02/28/theater/mary-said-what-she-said-review-huppert.html</link><description>在罗伯特·威尔逊（Robert Wilson）的作品中，伊莎贝尔·霍珀特（Isabelle Huppert）在舞台上到处都是，一次都在背诵一个可能会触及一切的不间断剧本。</description><pubDate>Fri, 28 Feb 2025 17:24:30 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2025/02/28/theater/mary-said-what-she-said-review-huppert.html</guid></item><item><title>约瑟夫·沃博（Joseph Wambaugh），作家有警察的视野，死于88</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2025/02/28/books/joseph-wambaugh-dead.html</link><description>在“闪光圆顶”和非小说类这样的小说中，他像《洋葱场》这样的作品，对执法的现实进行了苛刻，毫不掩饰的看法。</description><pubDate>Fri, 28 Feb 2025 18:00:26 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2025/02/28/books/joseph-wambaugh-dead.html</guid></item><item><title>读书俱乐部：阅读《汉康》的《我们不分开》，以及书评</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2025/02/28/books/review/we-do-not-part-han-kang-book-club.html</link><description>3月，书评书籍俱乐部将阅读和讨论“我们不分开”，这是诺贝尔奖获得者韩康的小说，讲述了历史，悲剧和记忆的工作。</description><pubDate>Fri, 28 Feb 2025 10:04:03 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2025/02/28/books/review/we-do-not-part-han-kang-book-club.html</guid></item></channel></rss>